    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "idk, it just feels like when people talk about \"strategic tariffs\" they're just making excuses for policies that actually hurt the working class. like, isn't the \"pragmatic path\" just a fancy way of saying we should stop trying to compete globally and just accept higher prices and less innovation?",
